Loading Data

Example BULK INSERT command:

BULK INSERT bronze.crm_cust_info
FROM 'C:\SQLData\cust_info.csv'
WITH (
    FORMAT = 'CSV',
    FIRSTROW = 2,
    TABLOCK
);

If using an older version of SQL Server:

BULK INSERT bronze.crm_cust_info
FROM 'C:\SQLData\cust_info.csv'
WITH (
    FIRSTROW = 2,
    FIELDTERMINATOR = ',',
    ROWTERMINATOR = '\n',
    TABLOCK
);
Prerequisites

Before running the project, ensure you have:

SQL Server 2019 or later (SQL Server 2022 recommended)
SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)
Read permission on the dataset folder
CSV files stored in a local directory accessible by SQL Server
Setup Instructions
Clone the repository.
Open SQL Server Management Studio.
Execute create_database.sql.
Execute create_tables.sql.
Update the CSV file paths in load_bronze.sql.
Run the Bronze layer load scripts.
Execute the Silver transformation scripts.
Create the Gold layer views.
Common Issues
Cannot bulk load because the file could not be opened

Possible causes:

Incorrect file path
SQL Server service account lacks permission
OneDrive file is not available offline
File is currently open in another application
Data Import Errors

Check that:

The CSV file contains a header row.
All rows have the same number of columns.
The correct field and row terminators are specified.
Data types match the destination table.
